atter how many Kobolds I lay to rest, The chamber of Nagafen heavies my chest;<br> For I come with a word of ice and comet, Lord of Dragons inhale your final breath.<br><br>How much can mundane people deny, the arcane powers which I provide?<br><br>Instead of raising a wielded blade, I read my grimoire, I sit and wait;<br> When those dumb barbarians hack and slash, I send a thunder - The ground shall shake.<br><br>I smile with anger, I grin with mischeif; I flick my fingers turning demons to ashes.<br><br>I sit back down, returning to my studies - Those demons haven't a chance to scream a sound.<br>  And those barbarians, bruised and beaten; Surely, uneeded acts of violence profound.<br><br>So I sit here, again, in meditation - under my spires, I ponder abomination.<br><br>I often wonder, Am I to be feared? I ramble off, I walk and sonder<br>  Perhaps they fear what they do not understand, I could care less I shall make them wonder.<br><br>I have nothing to prove - nothing at all. You say I'm weak and feeble, how dare you?<br><br>Somethings are better left unknown, I beleive I shall leave it at that - My mystery leaves me in solitary, leaving me behind - left alone.<br><br><br><br>~Gideon Leviticus<br>57 Wizard of Quellious - Apostle of Insanity.<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugideonleviticus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gideon Leviticus</A> at: 6/2/02 2:25:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugideonleviticus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gideon Leviticus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/02 2:27:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wheres.homestead.com/files/face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Wizard In Retrospect (poems)</span><hr size=1>  Tell-Tale of an Epic - Waiting for the Sprocket<br><br>I noticed a druid just passed the dock, Casting Wolf without much luck.<br>I snicker and pet my hungry drake. I speak so softly, &quot;Just simply wait!&quot;<br>I raise my arms in a film of ice, I release a blast of fury and might!<br>The druid jumps as his pants catch cold, he wants to fight? Oh... How Bold.<br><br>I stand up, adjusting my robes, I yawn and smile, my fists glowing orbs.<br>He offers a gesture, quite rude indeed! I asked politely do not impede!<br>I pointed out that I was awaiting the gnome, I hate those things, that's been known.<br>He asks me angrily, &quot;Why did you do that?&quot; I shrugged and nodded,&quot;To see how you'd react.&quot;<br><br>He yells and boasts that his power is great! Then I Fluxed him into the lake.<br>He stands up and casts a simple spell, again and again it simply fizzled.<br>I raised a brow and patted by drake, &quot;There there boy, look, it's Halfling steak.&quot;<br>The druid protested and roared in anger, I smiled at him and began to cast render...<br><br>The poor druid casted spells and persisted. I raised my brow as I had resisted.<br>&quot;Please now, druid, your spells did tickle; begone from my sight, Before I make a halfing pickle.&quot;<br>&quot;How dare you defy Tunare, you wizard!?&quot; I replied and smiled: &quot;Silence!  before I summon a blizzard!&quot;<br>I yawn again, I'm bored as usual. The Druid steps back and glares so casual.<br>I pet my drake and ask, &quot;Had enough?&quot; The Druid protests and casts a buff.<br><br>I end up rooting him and casting Druzzil, Before the rain ended a corpse of ash had crumbled.<br>&quot;Poor little Halfling, I had been playing...&quot; My drake on the other hand is still hungry and crying.<br>I look down and appologize, &quot;Sorry, but Halfling meat is tough - No lie.&quot;<br>I sat back down and to my surprise, that gnome walked up and to my side.<br><br>&quot;Hello there gnome,&quot; I smiled so happily. He looked me over and nodded properly.<br>I spoke to him once and received a sprocket, Stupid gnome mechanic breaking robots.<br>I sighed and nodded, I had to fix his machine, least he could do was offer pampering.<br>The gnome was silent as I left there, My next stop Cazic and finally Fear. <br><br><br> ... To be Continued<br><br>~Gideon Leviticus<br>57 Wizard of Quellious - Apostle of Insanity <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugideonleviticus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gideon Leviticus</A> at: 6/2/02 2:33:46 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm37.showPrevMessage?topicID=32.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm37.showNextMessage?topicID=32.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm37.emailToFriend?topicID=32.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm37.threadControl?topicID=32.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm37.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=32.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.